Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.49,0:06:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn’t say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:02.49,Endo,,0,0,0,,Damnit!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.36,0:06:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,100)}{\pos(373,387)\c&HC21F1D&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Cocorico \N\N\N {\c&H170E70&}Batsu Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.03,0:06:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.00,0:06:06.03,Endo,,0,0,0,,Daaaamnit!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.07,0:06:08.03,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You only said, “FO!”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.03,0:06:08.03,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Only “FO!”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:14.24,Hamada,,0,0,0,,{\pos(361,470)}You only said “FO!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:14.24,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\pos(361,470)\clip(254,457,462,471)}You only said “FO!”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:16.21,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,{\pos(361,439)}Why is it bad if I say only, “FO”?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.28,0:06:19.45,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It’s been decided, it’s Cocorico!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:20.11,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,No! I don’t want this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.65,0:06:22.65,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry! I’m really sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.65,0:06:24.65,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,I don’t want this!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.85,0:06:28.25,Hamada,,0,0,0,,But really, Tanaka, you were weird the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:31.69,Hamada,,0,0,0,,When someone points at you, you’re just like…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:37.36,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Alright, for Cocorico, go to Big Echo in Hibiya, the karaoke shop located along the main street.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:42.17,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Go to the second floor to sing and dance on the terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.17,0:06:44.77,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It’s a place where people will pass by the immediate vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.20,0:06:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\pos(167,48)}Batsu Game Location
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.20,0:06:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\pos(360,398)}Big Echo in Yurakucho on the second floor terrace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that it right there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:46.47,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.47,0:06:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That one, it says Big Echo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.04,0:06:50.04,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Get going then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:54.71,Hamada,,0,0,0,,On your way there, there’s tons of people waiting for the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:07:05.99,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(361,31)}*Translator’s notes: Miracle Type was a variety show that Cocorico hosted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:07:00.62,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Be sure to tell them that this is “Miracle Type”*
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:02.35,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,{\clip(168,441,182,471)\t(0,1000,\clip(168,441,682,471))}I’m just gonna say this is for “Gaki”.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:04.46,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Why can’t I just say it’s “Gaki no Tsukai”!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.46,0:07:06.46,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Why do I have to do something so embarrassing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.53,0:07:10.43,Endo,,0,0,0,,Oh geez, it’s so cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.43,0:07:12.03,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Wow, really cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.03,0:07:15.27,Endo,,0,0,0,,This is no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:17.50,Endo,,0,0,0,,Let’s finish this up and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:18.77,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.27,0:07:20.27,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,This is so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.91,0:07:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh wow, it’s outdoors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.87,0:07:26.04,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Yes indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:28.11,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,Hey, it’s looking kinda cool with the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.95,0:07:31.95,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,I’m a bit jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.82,0:07:40.82,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,It's starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\fs24\pos(281,369)}“Nagisa no Sinbad” (1977 - One-million copies sold)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(170,411)}{\fs24\pos(281,369)}Vocals: Cocorico
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.86,0:07:50.77,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,They look cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.77,0:07:52.77,Hamada,,0,0,0,,As if!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:09.00,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,They look like they’re representatives of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.38,0:08:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.69,0:08:52.46,Hamada,,0,0,0,,If you were going to do this, this was the ideal spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.86,0:08:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.06,0:08:57.40,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,{\clip(145,442,165,471)\t(0,1800,\clip(145,442,665,471))}Doing this at eye-level would be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.93,0:08:58.73,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.10,0:09:01.10,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Good job, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.97,0:09:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.97,0:09:04.97,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.11,0:09:09.88,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Well, it was good, wasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:14.15,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,It was amazing though, being exposed like that, just to let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:16.92,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was no good to be walking through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.92,0:09:19.02,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,We were caught at the traffic light.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.09,0:09:21.85,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Alright, well, that’s enough of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.19,0:09:25.19,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Continuing on, the next game is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:27.19,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Dandy Sakano Game!*
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:36.77,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(362,60)}*Translator’s notes: Dandy Sakano is another Japanese comedian, known for his catchphrase, “Gets!”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\pos(257,335)}Dandy Sakano Game Rules:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\pos(363,431)}Yell, “Dandy” then “Sakano”, in which you must point at a person after the name. The two people sitting next to the person who gets “Sakano” must say “Gets!” and pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.53,0:09:31.80,Hamada,,0,0,0,,This is just like the previous game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.80,0:09:35.33,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Dandy, Sakano, then both sides say, “Gets!”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.37,0:09:37.64,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.64,0:09:42.27,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Hold on, shall we shuffle then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.10,0:09:42.27,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Our seats?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.94,0:09:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let’s switch seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\move(1000,379,-200,379,25,1950)\fs48\3c&HBE87FA&\c&H2703CD&}Switch seats and game start!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.21,0:09:51.21,Junior,,0,0,0,,Hold on a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:53.02,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.05,0:09:55.05,Junior,,0,0,0,,Cocorico, what do you think of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.19,0:09:58.42,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,Wait, Komu, do I have something stuck here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.99,0:10:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell! No way. So cliche.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:10:00.43,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,You totally raised your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.86,0:10:03.86,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC21F1D&\3c&HFFFFFF&\pos(372,379)}Yamasaki & Komu: \N\N\NYamasaki is {\c&H55CCF1&\3c&H000000&}OUT
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.86,0:10:05.06,Endo,,0,0,0,,When you put your hand to your throat and say, “Komu, do I have something stuck here?”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.06,0:10:06.73,Endo,,0,0,0,,That was no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:07.80,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.73,0:10:07.87,Endo,,0,0,0,,That was the bad part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.87,0:10:09.50,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,That was really cliche.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.37,0:10:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Arita of Cream Stew still can’t seem to grasp the rules of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, Chihara Junior breaks his concentration and the guest duo are back in the heat of battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.98,0:10:24.98,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,Downtown is very strong.
