Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.43,0:12:22.73,Endo,,0,0,0,,Your performance, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Senile duo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.61,0:12:36.57,Arita,,0,0,0,,So embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.08,0:12:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(263,367)}{\fs24}“South Paw” (1978 - 1,460,000 copies sold)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.08,0:12:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(228,411)}{\fs24\}Vocals: Downtown
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh wow, they’re really doing it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.63,0:13:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re not even staying to watch!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.18,0:13:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.32,0:13:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No reaction at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren’t kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.42,0:13:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They won’t even laugh for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.42,0:13:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they’re creeped out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.62,0:13:26.86,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they’re probably creeped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.06,0:13:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No one’s watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.67,0:14:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What’re they doing right there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job back there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.41,0:14:24.15,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,That was amazing…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.15,0:14:26.68,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I knew that no one was laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.68,0:14:28.68,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,The people walking by didn’t care either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn’t watch, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.19,0:14:33.19,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You know, you actually don’t feel the cold out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.19,0:14:35.19,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you don’t feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:38.39,Hamada,,0,0,0,,When we first went outside, we were like, “Wow, it’s cold,” but yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:41.89,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,Because your body was burning with embarrassment?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.33,0:14:45.23,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,That was good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:49.47,Ueda,,0,0,0,,If that’s how they’ll react to Downtown, we’re screwed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:52.24,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Okay, I’ll be presenting the next game!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:56.81,Hamada,,0,0,0,,The next game is Antonio Inoki Dahhh!* Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:15:03.68,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(362,60)}*Translator’s notes: Antonio Inoki was a professional wrestler. He’s well-known for yelling 1, 2, 3, DAHHH!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:15:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\pos(257,335)} Antonio Inoki Dahhh! Game Rules:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:15:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}{\pos(363,431)}Yell, “Antonio” then “Inoki”, in which you must point at a person after the name. The two people sitting next to the person who gets “Inoki” must say “Dahhh!” and pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.31,0:15:00.62,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You already know the rules, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.62,0:15:03.68,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Antonio, then Inoki, then both sides say, “Dahhh!”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.35,0:15:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\move(1000,379,-200,379,25,1950)\fs48\3c&HBE87FA&\c&H2703CD&}Switch seats and game start!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.63,0:15:15.63,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You’re not saying anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.30,0:15:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(373,387)\c&HC21F1D&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Cream Stew: \N\N\NArita is {\c&H55CCF1&\3c&H000000&}OUT
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.17,0:15:18.97,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Come on…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.97,0:15:21.50,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,What are you, an orangutan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\c&HF77A62&\pos(364,316)}First to make 3 mistakes gets a batsu game!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(232,396)}Yamasaki &\N Komu:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(361,395)}Cream\N Stew:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(484,396)}Chihara\N Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.22,0:15:41.22,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Hold on, you’re way too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.22,0:15:42.86,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Too slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.36,0:15:44.36,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You’re just like, “Dahhhh…”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.86,0:15:46.13,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It should be more like “Antonio, Inoki, Dahhh!”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:47.63,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,That’s too fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.93,0:15:47.93,Ueda,,0,0,0,,We can’t do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.66,0:15:49.76,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,We can even do that! We can even do it, right guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.76,0:15:51.76,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Then show us an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.30,0:15:55.84,Ueda,,0,0,0,,You guys were all messed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.94,0:16:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, Yamasaki, who seemed to be good at the game, makes an unusual mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, Chihara Junior slips up which brings all three teams into a big close match.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.08,0:16:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\c&HF77A62&\pos(364,316)}First to make 3 mistakes gets a batsu game!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.08,0:16:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(232,396)}Yamasaki &\N Komu:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.08,0:16:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(361,395)}Cream\N Stew:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.08,0:16:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(484,396)}Chihara\N Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:24.10,Hamada,,0,0,0,,That’s enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.10,0:16:24.96,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,That’s enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.96,0:16:27.37,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,{\clip(199,444,220,471)\t(0,1300,\clip(199,444,620,471)}Are you guys the bus’ engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.70,0:16:32.44,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Is that what this bus is running on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.67,0:16:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at this stage of the game, Chihara Junior can’t follow the rhythm and gets 2 mistakes in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.36,0:16:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Chihara Brothers are in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\c&HF77A62&\pos(364,316)}First to make 3 mistakes gets a batsu game!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(232,396)}Yamasaki &\N Komu:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(361,395)}Cream\N Stew:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(484,396)}Chihara\N Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:53.49,Seiji,,0,0,0,,Wasn’t that too slow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.49,0:16:55.49,Hamada,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.06,0:16:56.06,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Why are you stopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.99,0:16:58.73,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Why did you stop?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.73,0:17:00.33,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,That was just fine, wasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.63,0:17:00.33,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,That was fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.33,0:17:02.33,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Chihara Brothers!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.43,0:17:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,100)}{\pos(373,387)\c&HC21F1D&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Chihara Brothers \N\N\N {\c&H170E70&}Batsu Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:08.44,Seiji,,0,0,0,,That was totally… Totally off! Wasn’t it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:10.44,Endo,,0,0,0,,No no no, that was not off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.97,0:17:12.74,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Ehhh? How was that off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:16.05,Ueda,,0,0,0,,What is up with your phrasing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.21,0:17:19.35,Seiji,,0,0,0,,It’s all your damn fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:21.48,Arita,,0,0,0,,I’ll apologize if it makes you feel any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.48,0:17:23.19,Ueda,,0,0,0,,You don’t need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.19,0:17:25.76,Ueda,,0,0,0,,In fact, you should be pissed off. He’s just accusing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.76,0:17:34.61,Hamada,,0,0,0,,For Chihara Brothers, go to Japan’s #1 fashionable area Daikanyama* and sing and dance at an outdoor cafe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.76,0:17:34.61,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(362,60)}*Translator’s notes: Daikanyama is a very chic and trendy area in Shibuya, Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:34.63,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t want that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.83,0:17:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(163,49)}Batsu game location
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.83,0:17:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(364,402)}Cafe terrace “Lloyd Cafe” in Daikanyama
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.33,0:17:38.37,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It’s this place, here, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.37,0:17:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.47,0:17:40.74,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It’s completely empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.04,0:17:45.11,Hamada,,0,0,0,,The people inside the cafe are really staring.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.41,0:17:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.71,0:17:47.08,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Just hurry up and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:48.18,Junior,,0,0,0,,Oh hell
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:49.48,Junior,,0,0,0,,{\pos(359,469)}So cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:49.48,Seiji,,0,0,0,,{\pos(359,469)\clip(307,456,403,469)}So cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.48,0:17:53.48,Endo,,0,0,0,,Here they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.58,0:17:55.78,Endo,,0,0,0,,They’re hesitating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.78,0:17:58.78,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,These guys, you know, they’re brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This must suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.69,0:18:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(227,364)}{\fs24}“UFO” (1977 - 1,550,000 copies sold)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.69,0:18:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(189,410)}{\fs24\}Vocals: Chihara Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.13,0:18:11.13,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,This is grossing me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re causing a disturbance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.82,0:18:38.82,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,They’re brothers, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.30,0:18:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t watch this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.20,0:18:46.50,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Me either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.63,0:19:16.13,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Should we just leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.93,0:19:17.93,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Start driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.93,0:19:19.63,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Get the bus going!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.00,0:19:19.63,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Let’s go, let’s go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.03,0:19:24.13,Seiji,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,297)\c&HA2150E&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Chihara Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(367,403)\c&H7E2CC9&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Left behind in Daikanyama while still dressed as Pink Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.67,0:19:27.17,Seiji,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you doing?!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.17,0:19:28.21,Junior,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.21,0:19:29.54,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Bye bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.84,0:19:31.07,Seiji,,0,0,0,,What the hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.08,0:19:38.68,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Alright, we’ve only got 1 game left and for the last round, it’ll be Takeda Tetsuya Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.08,0:19:38.68,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(362,60)}*Translator’s notes: Takeda Tetsuya is an actor and singer, most well-known for his role as Kinpachi Sensei in the Kinpachi Sensei J-drama series.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.85,0:19:38.68,Endo,,0,0,0,,This is a standard one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.72,0:19:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last round of the batsu game, there’s only 2 teams competing. Arita, still unable to get the hang of the game, is out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.29,0:19:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Continuing on, Yamasaki makes an unlikely mistake and the game alternates the losses!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.60,0:19:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, when the game switches over to Senda Mitsuo*...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.60,0:20:00.07,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(362,60)}Translator's notes: Senda Mitsuo is a voice actor who has been voice acting in many major animes and dubbed for big Hollywood movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.57,0:19:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355,400)\c&HD91732&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Cream Stew\N\N\N\N{\c&H170E70&}IN DANGER!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.84,0:20:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cream Stew is in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:03.41,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Alright, the game might or might not end here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\c&HF77A62&\pos(364,316)}Cream Stew in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(254,395)}Cream\N Stew:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\fs22\pos(453,395)}Yamasaki &\N Komu:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.41,0:20:06.48,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Next is Shimura Ken Aiin.*
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.41,0:20:06.48,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(361,79)}*Translator’s notes: Shimura Ken is a comedian who usually plays the foolish character. Aiin is a nonsensical phrase that he made up and became popular in Japanese media.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.39,0:20:23.39,Ueda,,0,0,0,,What the hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.56,0:20:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,100)}{\pos(373,387)\c&HC21F1D&\3c&HFFFFFF&}Cream Stew \N\N\N {\c&H170E70&}Batsu Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:27.56,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Get a grip, goddamnit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:30.77,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Arita, it’s a miracle that you even made it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.44,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Alright, now for Cream Stew.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.44,0:20:35.94,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Location is Odaiba.*
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.44,0:20:41.44,Translator's Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(370,54)}*Translator’s note: Odaiba is a city in Tokyo, built on an artificial island. It is a major commercial and leisure area with accessible seashores.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:38.04,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Odaiba is a tough one…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.34,0:20:41.18,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Not only that, it’s at the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:44.08,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Why the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:44.08,Arita,,0,0,0,,There’s no way anyone would be there, right? Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.08,0:20:46.08,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,It’s pitch black outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:47.55,Ueda,,0,0,0,,We’ll just look like we’re having a normal Pink Lady practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:50.05,Ueda,,0,0,0,,In such a place, in such a situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:53.12,Endo,,0,0,0,,What’s going to happen? The bus stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.65,0:20:53.90,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It’s right there. Right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.89,0:20:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(163,49)}Batsu game location
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.89,0:20:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(364,402)}Sandy shores of the Odaiba Beachfront Park
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.26,0:20:57.36,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,There isn’t even one person around!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:20:59.63,Ueda,,0,0,0,,There really is nobody around!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.96,0:21:03.87,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Oh god, it’s so cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.87,0:21:05.33,Ueda,,0,0,0,,So damn cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.70,0:21:06.90,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.90,0:21:09.07,Endo,,0,0,0,,Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.14,0:21:10.14,Ueda,,0,0,0,,It’s so damn cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.74,0:21:13.07,Ueda,,0,0,0,,So cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.07,0:21:15.88,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Why is it only Ueda who keeps saying it’s cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.71,0:21:16.41,Hamada,,0,0,0,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.01,0:21:18.01,Ueda,,0,0,0,,So cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.41,0:21:20.05,Hamada,,0,0,0,,There must be something wrong with Arita.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:20.05,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Something’s wrong with his bodily senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(276,364)}{\fs24}“Carmen ‘77” (1977 - 660,000 copies sold)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)\pos(224,411)}{\fs24\}Vocals: Cream Stew
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.10,0:21:41.03,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Fast, very fast
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.83,0:21:41.83,Hamada,,0,0,0,,This is pretty good!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.99,0:22:03.99,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Whoa, amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.10,0:22:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, people are actually passing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:19.00,Hamada,,0,0,0,,(Hamada also singing along)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.91,0:22:24.91,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Arita is really tone-deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.43,0:22:42.16,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Something ran by, a dog ran by!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.86,0:22:44.76,Ueda,,0,0,0,,We did it with all of our strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.76,0:22:46.23,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.23,0:22:48.23,Ueda,,0,0,0,,We were right over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.23,0:22:50.23,Yamasaki,,0,0,0,,Huh? We didn’t notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.70,0:22:50.70,Ueda,,0,0,0,,We were there, if you just looked to the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.44,0:22:54.47,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that, we were discussing what to do next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.47,0:22:56.77,Ueda,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to do that now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.77,0:22:58.81,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Someone better confirm that we did the entire song.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:01.08,Ueda,,0,0,0,,Like someone saying, “They did it!”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.28,0:23:01.61,Arita,,0,0,0,,Just leave it, don’t say any more.
